/*!
\page code-block-test Code Block Tests

Test the appearance of code blocks in the documentation output.


<h3>Dash Test</h3>

Test one is using an ampersand and ndash which looks like this: &ndash;&ndash;prefix


Test two shows an ampersand and ndash text in a code block, these are displayed verbatim.

\code
&ndash;&ndash;prefix $HOME/cs_lib
\endcode

<br>
Test three uses two plain dashs like this: --prefix

Test four show what two plain dashs will look like in a code block, these are displayed verbatim.

\code
--prefix $HOME/cs_lib
\endcode


<br>


<h3>Code Block Tilde Test</h3>

Test five is contained in the following code block. The tilde should only appear one time.


\code
class MyClass {

   public:
      MyInteger();
      ~MyInteger();

   private:
      int & d_intValue;
};
\endcode


<br>


<h3>Back Slash Test</h3>

Test six has been set up to show how a back slash appears in a code block. The following text should show three single back
slash escaped characters on the declaration. The lines declaringx1, x2, x3, and x4 should each show a back slash
followed by a single character.

\code
   QString regexp = "\b\d+\b";

   QString x1 = "\>";
   QString x2 = "\<";
   QString x3 = "\\";
   QString x3 = "\r";

\endcode


<br><br>


*/


